window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Wind down by escaping into nature. Part soundscape and part bedtime story, <i>The Sleeping World</i> is an intimate journey through ecologies around the world.</p> <p>North Ronaldsay sheep have been roaming the shores of a Scottish isle for centuries. They outnumber people there by more than twenty to one. While most sheep graze in fields, the North Ronaldsay are a breed apart: they forage seaweed on the rocky beach. In this episode, we follow a lamb as she crosses the island’s ancient stone dyke and sees the ocean for the first time.</p> <p>This is the world in its natural state, defined by seasons, routines, and cycles. By the time this lamb is ready to let the waves lull her to sleep, you’ll be drifting off too.</p> <p><b><i>Produced by</i></b><i> Audible and Mumble Media</i></p> <p><b><i>Written by</i></b><i> Cara Ehlenfeldt</i></p> <p><b><i>Narrated by</i></b><i> Cynthia Kimola</i></p> <p><b><i>Executive Producers for Mumble Media:</i></b><i> Cara Ehlenfeldt and Jake Young</i></p> <p><b><i>Executive Producer for Audible:</i></b><i> Anna Stitt</i></p> <p><b><i>Sound Design and Mix: </i></b><i>Mumble Media</i></p> <p><b><i>Additional Recordings: </i></b><i>Nicholas Jourjine</i></p> <p><b><i>The Mumble Media team is </i></b><i>Jaymeson Catsouphes, Cara Ehlenfeldt, Liz Mak, Lee Mengistu, David Tatasciore, Renée Vargas, Jake Young, and Sharif Youssef</i></p> <p><b><i>North Ronaldsay Sheep Consultant: </i></b><i>Michael Scott</i></p> <p><b><i>Fact-Checker: </i></b><i>Andrea López-Cruzado</i></p> <p><b><i>Head of Creative Development: </i></b><i>Kate Navin</i></p> <p><b><i>Head of Audible Originals, North America: </i></b><i>Marshall Lewy</i></p> <p><b><i>Chief Content Officer: </i></b><i>Rachel Ghiazza</i></p>"; 
